      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that universal healthcare stifles innovation and leads to government mismanagement is a common misconception perpetuated by special interest groups. In reality, countries with universal healthcare have seen significant investments in medical research and development, and the US is actually one of the most expensive healthcare systems in the world, with some of the worst health outcomes. The myth of \"government mismanagement\" is often used to justify the status quo of a multi-trillion-dollar healthcare industry controlled by corporate interests.",
